abstract: An American diplomat's wife who left the U.K. after being involved in a road accident that killed a British teenager has been charged with causing death by dangerous driving, British prosecutors said Friday.
snippet: An American diplomat's wife who left the U.K. after being involved in a road accident that killed a British teenager has been charged with causing death by dangerous driving, British prosecutors said Friday.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — An American diplomat's wife who left the U.K. after being involved in a road accident that killed a British teenager has been charged with causing death by dangerous driving, British prosecutors said Friday.
headline_main: UK Charges US Diplomat's Wife Over Teen's Death in Crash
headline_print_headline: UK Charges US Diplomat's Wife Over Teen's Death in Crash

abstract: Li Xiuping, a reporter for a state-run newspaper, has helped organize an online coalition trying to change China’s marriage laws.
snippet: Li Xiuping, a reporter for a state-run newspaper, has helped organize an online coalition trying to change China’s marriage laws.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — For the first seven months after her divorce, Li Xiuping thought her former husband had disappeared from her life. Then came the phone call that turned Ms. Li, a journalist for a state-run newspaper in Beijing, into a dogged activist for the economic rights of Chinese women.

abstract: A deadly shooting at a city building in Winston-Salem, North Carolina was an act of “workplace violence" by one city employee who targeted a co-worker he'd disliked for a long time, police said Friday.

abstract: Ford is recalling more than 600,000 midsize sedans in the U.S. to fix a problem with the brakes that can increase stopping distance and possibly cause a crash.
snippet: Ford is recalling more than 600,000 midsize sedans in the U.S. to fix a problem with the brakes that can increase stopping distance and possibly cause a crash.
lead_paragraph: DEARBORN, Mich. — Ford is recalling more than 600,000 midsize sedans in the U.S. to fix a problem with the brakes that can increase stopping distance and possibly cause a crash.
headline_main: Ford Recalls 600,000 Midsize Cars in US to Fix Brake Problem
headline_print_headline: Ford Recalls 600,000 Midsize Cars in US to Fix Brake Problem

abstract: Prince Philip, the husband of Queen Elizabeth II, was admitted to a London hospital Friday “as a precautionary measure,” Buckingham Palace said.
snippet: Prince Philip, the husband of Queen Elizabeth II, was admitted to a London hospital Friday “as a precautionary measure,” Buckingham Palace said.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Prince Philip, the husband of Queen Elizabeth II, was admitted to a London hospital Friday “as a precautionary measure,” Buckingham Palace said.
headline_main: Palace: Prince Philip in Hospital as 'Precautionary Measure'
headline_print_headline: Palace: Prince Philip in Hospital as 'Precautionary Measure'

abstract: To make repairs, Westbury House on Long Island needed a supply of Collyweston slate, but all of the mines had closed decades earlier. Then one reopened.
snippet: To make repairs, Westbury House on Long Island needed a supply of Collyweston slate, but all of the mines had closed decades earlier. Then one reopened.
lead_paragraph: Nobody ever said that New York was a movable feast, but one rich family did its best to make it one a century ago by packing up an entire, sumptuous Fifth Avenue dining room and reassembling it in the country.
headline_main: For a Roof in Old Westbury, N.Y., a Singular Slate From England
headline_print_headline: The Hunt for a New Roof Extends to Britain

abstract: Germany's upper house of parliament has approved a plan to make rail travel cheaper as part of a package of measures to combat climate change.
snippet: Germany's upper house of parliament has approved a plan to make rail travel cheaper as part of a package of measures to combat climate change.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Germany's upper house of parliament has approved a plan to make rail travel cheaper as part of a package of measures to combat climate change.
headline_main: Germany OKs Cheaper Train Tickets in Plan to Lower Emissions
headline_print_headline: Germany OKs Cheaper Train Tickets in Plan to Lower Emissions
